doc.after: Many hypotheses have been advanced as to what functions the cranial crest of Parasaurolophus performed, but most have been discredited.[3][28] It is now believed that it may have had several functions: visual display for identifying species and sex, sound amplification for communication, and thermoregulation. It is not clear which was most significant at what times in the evolution of the crest and its internal nasal passages.[29]
